<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,330,1678,1702]" pageId="6" pageNumber="333">Identification.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished from others of its genus by the frons reddish or brownish, the thorax with a comma-shaped black mark extending across the metepisternum below the spiracle, the large basal orange spot on its hind wings, and the abdomen reddish except segments 8–10 which have black spots (
<bibRefCitation author="Borror DJ" box="[175,311,1886,1910]" pageId="6" pageNumber="333" pagination="1 - 286" refId="ref6524" refString="Borror DJ (1942) A revision of Libelluline genus Erythrodiplax (Odo- nata). Ohio State University Graduate Studies, Contributions in Zoology and Entomolology 4: 1 - 286. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / aesa / 36.3.587" type="journal article" year="1942">Borror 1942</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
